Higher WIS/INT improves the chances for a skill-up.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That's not what the tradeskill community thinks, Anna. Only the skill influences the chances of a successful combine. The higher of wis/int for all skills, and an additional stat for some skills, determine the chances of a skill-up. In the case of flecthing (and poison making) DEX is the secondary attribute, as STR is for smithing. <br>
<br>
Gariet, /bonk<br>
Ask your fella rogues before burning all that time and plat. For the last several points, go to the trainer and train them - costs a bit over 100 plat a point, but sooooo worth it.  Both Stanos himself, and the PoK trainers can train poisonmaking to 250.<br>
