<br>
And the buildings.  Holy crap.  This is what you do if you wanna build a building.  Buy a plot of land from npc.  You now have a little sign in the world with a dirt outline of where your structure is to be.  Double clicking brings up the design window which shows among other things, the required materials.  There is usually around 10 different typs of basic materials needed for any give building, and lots of them.  It's not something one person can feasably do on their own.  What you do is drop money on the plot of land, and set your own payout prices for materials.  That allows anybody to wander by, and sell some of their resources to the structure and get paid automatically.<br>
<br>
I saw a player built bridge a few days ago.  Massive bridge, like, you can't see the end with clip plane.  Kind of bridge that is on par with the iceclad / EW bridge.  I mean holy crap.  Oh and if you contribute resources to construction of buildings like that, your name is inscribed on it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I think EQ2 will have a similiar system of tradeskilling.  Mainly because Horizons hit beta first and there is probably some SOE janitor that got into beta for it.<br>
<br>
